/#dynamic-bayesian-networks" title=3D"Direct link to heading">=E2=80=8B</a>=
</h2><p><strong>Dynamic Bayesian networks</strong> (DBNs) are used for mode=
ling times series and sequences.
They extend the concept of standard Bayesian networks with time.  In Bayes =
Server, time has been a native part of the platform
from day 1, so you can even construct probability distributions such as P(X=
<!-- -->[t=3D0]<!-- -->, X<!-- -->[t+5]<!-- -->, Y | Z<!-- -->[t=3D2]<!-- -=
